```sql
-- int_customer_channel_deduped.sql
-- Deduplicate customer channels to one per customer
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        customer_id,
        channel,
        attributed_at,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY customer_id
            ORDER BY attributed_at DESC
        ) AS row_num
    FROM {{ ref('stg_customer_channels') }}
)
SELECT
    customer_id,
    channel
FROM source
WHERE row_num = 1
```

-- fct_revenue_by_channel_city.sql
-- Customer revenue aggregated by attribution channel and store city
SELECT
    COALESCE(cc.channel, '(unknown)') AS channel,
    COALESCE(s.city, '(unknown)') AS city,
    SUM(t.amount) AS total_revenue,
    COUNT(t.transaction_id) AS transaction_count,
    COUNT(DISTINCT t.customer_id) AS unique_customers
FROM {{ ref('stg_transactions') }} t
LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_stores') }} s
    ON s.store_id = t.store_id
LEFT JOIN {{ ref('int_customer_channel_deduped') }} cc
    ON cc.customer_id = t.customer_id
GROUP BY
    COALESCE(cc.channel, '(unknown)'),
    COALESCE(s.city, '(unknown)')
ORDER BY
    total_revenue DESC
